1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Mojo-Mojo-Mojo-Spy

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Mojo-Mojo-Mojo-Spy

3
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
This world is colorful and bright

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
But what truly dazzles our sight

5
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Use your heart to see it clear

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
The truth is always near

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Hey you good or bad, truly

8
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Can't escape the soul's smoky haze

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Gather all your courage, be brave

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Maybe you can save the world today

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

13
00:00:53,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

14
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
The vanished tears

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
I am honored to announce that the first stop of the Angel's Tears gem world tour

16
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Will be held at the Banana Museum in this city

17
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,000
That's what I'm after

18
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Locky Qi, hurry up!

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
I stayed up late watching Smile Match last night

20
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,000
And you dragged me out early this morning

21
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,000
You're so mean

22
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
There's a really cool exhibition today

23
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Angel's Tears

24
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Boring

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,000
I'm definitely not going

26
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Go ahead.

27
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,000
No way.

28
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Come on, come on.

29
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Absolutely not.

30
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Please, please, please.

31
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,000
But if you buy me ice cream, I'll go with you.

32
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Ice cream's here!

33
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,159
Hey, watch where you're going!

34
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:34,699
Can't you drive properly?

35
00:02:34,699 --> 00:02:35,960
You're driving me crazy!

36
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,360
Sorry, please step back.

37
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,879
Everyone, stay calm.

38
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:43,379
Thanks.

39
00:02:43,379 --> 00:02:45,819
Step back and cooperate with us.

40
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,280
I'm going in anyway.

41
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:55,280
Let us in!

42
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,280
Awesome!

43
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,020
They're all flying!

44
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:14,719
So many cute exhibits!

45
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:16,140
Jingjing loves it here!

46
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:18,240
So adorable.

47
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:24,200
This in front of us should be the Angel's Tears, right?

48
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,780
Wait, where's the gem?

49
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,560
Stop right there.

50
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,099
What do you think you're doing?

51
00:03:39,099 --> 00:03:42,939
Let me go.

52
00:03:42,939 --> 00:03:45,260
What are you doing?

53
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:50,840
Just as I expected.

54
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,280
The criminal will always return to the crime scene.

55
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,760
Who are you?

56
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,480
Kid, you have eyes but can't see Mount Tai.

57
00:03:56,480 --> 00:04:00,340
I am the legendary detective who strikes fear into criminals across the alert zone—

58
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:01,780
Inspector Sima.

59
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:03,319
What lousy detective?

60
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:05,020
Let me go.

61
00:04:05,020 --> 00:04:07,159
How dare you insult a police officer!

62
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:14,159
Hold him tight, don't let him escape.

63
00:04:23,159 --> 00:04:24,560
Huh? Why them?

64
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,800
So young and already on the path of theft.

65
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,699
How did your parents raise you?

66
00:04:32,699 --> 00:04:33,920
You've got the wrong people.

67
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,620
Please let them go.

68
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:37,180
Who are you?

69
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:38,980
What makes you say we've got the wrong people?

70
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:41,280
I'm international detective Jimmy Chen.

71
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:43,500
You've arrested my little nephew.

72
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,120
Stop messing around.

73
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,160
I warned you before—

74
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,980
Your mind isn't cut out for solving cases.

75
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,980
Yes.

76
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:00,020
Detective Chen, welcome.

77
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:01,220
Sorry to trouble you again.

78
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:06,220
[Shoving sounds]

79
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:08,220
Wah wah wah, Uncle!

80
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:12,440
You bunch of bad guys!

81
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:14,360
Why are you picking on us?

82
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:17,200
No, no, no, it wasn't me!

83
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,500
Locky Qi, you've got it wrong.

84
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,500
They're police officers.

85
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,900
Here's what happened:

86
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,900
Last night, the precious gem, Angel's Tears,

87
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:28,460
had just been delivered to the exhibition hall when it mysteriously vanished.

88
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:29,920
The police are investigating.

89
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,040
You barged in,

90
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,600
so of course you're suspects.

91
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,319
Let me introduce you.

92
00:05:34,319 --> 00:05:36,660
This is Mr. K, the agent for this exhibition.

93
00:05:36,660 --> 00:05:41,000
Hello.

94
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,879
And this is the head of security here, Lei Jie.

95
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:45,680
Greetings, everyone.

96
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,939
The vault door holding the gem

97
00:05:47,939 --> 00:05:50,600
requires both of their personal keys to open.

98
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,340
But on the night of the incident,

99
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:53,780
both of them were elsewhere.

100
00:05:53,780 --> 00:06:00,620
If the gem can't be returned to my country...

101
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:01,759
What should I do?

102
00:06:01,759 --> 00:06:04,000
Jimmy,

103
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,240
what do you think?

104
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,060
Tricking these surveillance devices

105
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:09,160
isn't that hard.

106
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,000
I just connected my computer to the museum's mainframe

107
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:12,939
and found some issues.

108
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:13,939
Everyone, come take a look.

109
00:06:17,939 --> 00:06:18,540
Where's Jingjing?

110
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:26,980
Jingjing,

111
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:29,819
where are you?

112
00:06:30,819 --> 00:06:31,060
Jingjing!

113
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:32,060
Jingjing!

114
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:39,060
That guy looks really familiar.

115
00:06:41,060 --> 00:06:43,060
Hey, isn't he the jerk who hit me with his car?

116
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:45,060
What's he doing here?

117
00:06:46,060 --> 00:06:48,060
Target locked.

118
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:50,060
Located at twelve o'clock.

119
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:51,060
Copy that.

120
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:01,560
After investigation,

121
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:04,220
I found that a hacker broke into the mainframe controlling the museum's vault.

122
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:06,740
His exact goal is still unclear,

123
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:09,980
but I suspect this hacker

124
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:13,660
is connected to the gem theft case.

125
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:18,379
The hacker is starting to break in again.

126
00:07:20,379 --> 00:07:21,340
Everyone, stay calm.

127
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:23,520
I'll deploy the fireproof vehicle to deal with him.

128
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:34,220
So this is what a hacker battle looks like?

129
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:54,340
What's that sneaky villain up to?

130
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:08,340
Hmm, he's waltzing right in.

131
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:12,340
The poor intruder—I've already cornered him.

132
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:16,340
Wow, Detective Chen really knows his way around hackers.

133
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:20,340
Haha, it's nothing, nothing at all.

134
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:26,340
Ah, the hacker got away!

135
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:36,340
Cool, successfully hacked the mainframe. The vault door's about to open.

136
00:08:44,340 --> 00:08:46,340
This kid's got some skills.

137
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:48,340
He actually made the door open by itself.

138
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:50,340
He's definitely up to no good.

139
00:08:50,340 --> 00:08:52,340
I need to find Uncle fast.

140
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:58,340
Jingjing, this is urgent.

141
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:00,340
Go get Uncle right now.

142
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:02,340
Jingjing.

143
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:07,340
Juice.

144
00:09:07,340 --> 00:09:09,340
All gone.

145
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:19,340
Is this enough?

146
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:31,340
I order you to find Uncle immediately.

147
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:34,340
Roger that!

148
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:43,340
He's already out.

149
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:45,340
What now?

150
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:54,480
I really don't want to be alone and lonely.

151
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,920
But life

152
00:09:57,920 --> 00:10:02,399
can sometimes be a little unhappy.

153
00:10:02,399 --> 00:10:05,519
Saying goodbye to today

154
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:09,920
always feels a bit sad.

155
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:13,320
Look at tomorrow

156
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:17,660
waving to me from the horizon.

157
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:21,379
Every day, as the sun rises and sets,

158
00:10:21,379 --> 00:10:25,399
I turn time into more dreams.

159
00:10:25,399 --> 00:10:30,439
Looking forward to every second and moment of life,

160
00:10:30,439 --> 00:10:37,139
bright eyes are sparkling.

161
00:10:37,139 --> 00:10:40,519
A smile that greets the sunlight,

162
00:10:40,519 --> 00:10:45,740
stepping through the silent crossroads.

163
00:10:47,659 --> 00:10:51,480
Drop dead.

164
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,779
You are now the prime suspect.

165
00:10:56,779 --> 00:10:59,639
Please come with us.